'''AdvancED''' is a non-profit, non-governmental organization that [[Pre-tertiary education accreditation|accredits primary and secondary schools]] throughout the [[United States]] and internationally.<ref name=Citizen>{{cite news|title=All 31 Coweta Schools to Get Another 5{{hyphen}}Year  Accreditation|author=Nelms, Ben|date=October 3, 2010|newspaper=The Citizen|location=Fayette, GA|url=http://www.thecitizen.com/articles/10-03-2010/all-31-coweta-schools-get-another-5-year-accreditation |accessdate=October 6, 2010}}</ref>  AdvancED was formed in 2006 by the consolidation of the pre-college divisions of two of the U.S. [[regional accreditation]] organizations: the Commission on Accreditation and School Improvement of the [[North Central Association of Colleges and Schools]] (NCA CASI), and the  Council on Accreditation and School Improvement of the [[Southern Association of Colleges and Schools]] (SACS CASI).<ref name="Citizen" /> In 2012 the [[Northwest Accreditation Commission]] (NWAC) joined AdvancED.<ref>{{cite web|author=www.northwestaccreditation.org |url=http://www.northwestaccreditation.org/ |title=Welcome |publisher=www.northwestaccreditation.org |date= |accessdate=December 26, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710185729/http://www.northwestaccreditation.org/ |archivedate=July 10, 2009}}</ref><ref name="ABOUT">{{cite web |url=http://www.advanc-ed.org/about-us |title=AdvancED: About Us |website= advanc-ed.org |accessdate=May 2, 2018}}</ref>

At the end of the 2010{{hyphen}}2011 AdvancED reported that it served more than 27,000 institutions including 3,000 that were engaged in school improvement but not yet accredited.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.advanc-ed.org/webfm_send/314 |title=AdvancED 2010{{hyphen}}2011 Annual Report |publisher=AdvancED|accessdate=May 2, 2018 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120510150920/http://advanc-ed.org/webfm_send/314 |archivedate=May 10, 2012}}</ref>

The organization has headquarters in [[Alpharetta, Georgia]] and [[Tempe, Arizona]].

