{{BLP sources|date=December 2010}} '''Carol Z. Garrison''' was the 6th [[University President|President]] of the [[University of Alabama at Birmingham]]. The Board of Trustees of the [[University of Alabama System]] unanimously voted to appoint her to the office on July 23, 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://main.it.uab.edu/Sites/MediaRelations/articles/43137/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-04-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100627000438/http://main.it.uab.edu/Sites/MediaRelations/articles/43137/ |archivedate=2010-06-27 |df= }}</ref> She stepped down from presidency on August 16, 2012.<ref>http://blog.al.com/spotnews/2012/08/uab_president_carol_garrison_s_1.html</ref>
She is a member of [[Phi Beta Kappa Society|Phi Beta Kappa]], [[Sigma Xi]], and [[Delta Omega]]. She was twice honored as the [[Carolina Distinguished Professor]].<ref>http://www.uab.edu/newsarchive/43137-garrison-named-uab-president</ref><ref>http://www.louisvillecardinal.com/2002/03/garrison-named-acting-president/</ref>
==Prior employment== * 1976-1978 – Assistant Professor of [[Nursing]], [[University of Alabama at Birmingham]] * 1978-1982 – Assistant Professor, [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]] * 1982-1992 – Faculty Member, [[University of South Carolina]] * 1992-1994 – [[Professor]] & [[Chairperson|Chair]] of [[Epidemiology]] and [[Biostatistics]], [[University of South Carolina]] * 1994-1997 – [[Provost (education)|Associate Provost]] & [[dean (education)|Dean]] of the [[Graduate School]], [[University of South Carolina]] * 1997-2002 – [[Provost (education)|Provost]], [[University of Louisville]] * 2002-2002 – Acting president, [[University of Louisville]]
==Education== * 1974 – [[Bachelor's Degree]], [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]] * 1976 – [[Master's Degree]], [[University of Alabama at Birmingham|UAB]] School of [[Nursing]] * 1978 – [[Pediatrics|Pediatric]] Nurse Practitioner Certificate, [[University of Alabama at Birmingham|UAB]] School of [[Nursing]] * 1982 – [[Doctor of Philosophy|Ph.D.]] in [[Epidemiology]], [[University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill]]
