The '''Critical Race Studies in Education Association''' is an American interdisciplinary organization dedicated to the study of [[critical race theory]] and the promotion of [[racial justice]] in [[education]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www1.cuny.edu/mu/ncc/2014/07/31/guttman-students-attend-critical-race-studies-in-education-association/ |title=Guttman Students Attend Critical Race Studies in Education Association National Conference –  Stella and Charles Guttman Community College News – Guttman Community College |date=2014-07-31 |website=www1.cuny.edu |language=en-US |access-date=2017-12-18}}</ref> It was founded in 2007 and has held a conference annually since then.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZfKoAAAAQBAJ |title=Race Frameworks: A Multidimensional Theory of Racism and Education |last=Leonardo |first=Zeus |date=2013 |publisher=Teachers College Press |isbn=9780807754627 |pages=11 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WAUoDwAAQBAJ |title=Researching Race in Education: Policy, Practice and Qualitative Research |last=Dixon |first=Adrienne D. |date=2014-06-01 |publisher=IAP |isbn=9781623966782 |pages=53 |language=en}}</ref>
