The '''Higher National Technical Education Certificate''', abbreviated as '''HNTec''', is a post-secondary [[Vocational education|vocational]] qualification in [[Brunei]]. It is a Level 4 qualification in the country's current [[Brunei Darussalam National Qualifications Framework|national qualifications framework]] and awarded by the [[Brunei Darussalam Technical and Vocational Education Council]] (BDTVEC).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ibte.edu.bn/2015/02/18/post-secondary-progression-opportunities/|title=IBTE : Institute of Brunei Technical Education - Inspiring Bruneians Towards Excellence|last=IBTE|website=ibte.edu.bn|language=en|access-date=2018-03-20}}</ref> It is equivalent to the [[National Diploma (Brunei)|National Diploma]], although the latter has been phased out in government institutions. HNTec programmes are offered in the [[Institute of Brunei Technical Education]] and generally last two years. The qualification allows entry into Level 5-equivalent qualification, previously the [[Higher National Diploma]]. HNTec is the continuation of the [[National Technical Education Certificate]] (NTec).

