{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 345 |organ = SC |date = 17 January |year = 1974 |meeting = 1,761 |code = S/RES/345 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/345(1974) |for = |abstention = |against = |subject = Chinese language in Security Council |result = Adopted |image = Hanzi.svg |caption = Chinese ([[Traditional Chinese characters|traditional]] and [[Simplified Chinese characters|simplified]]) }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[List of UN Security Council Resolutions|Security Council Resolution]] 345''', adopted on January 17, 1974, after a resolution from the [[United Nations General Assembly|General Assembly]], the Council decided to expand that working languages of the Security Council to include [[Chinese language|Chinese]]. Along with Chinese, the other four working languages of the Council were [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]], [[Russian language|Russian]] and [[Spanish language|Spanish]].
The resolution was adopted without vote.
